description.narrative:
- Access to finance: The Project will enhance access to financial services to micro and small enterprises as well as the agriculture sector, which is expected to lead to job creation, income generation and inclusive growth in Senegal; 
- Demonstration Effect: This is IFC's first engagement with a financial cooperative in West Africa, and the project is expected to have a positive impact on the perception of the commercial viability of microfinance cooperatives in general and UM-ACEP in particular, and send a strong signal on IFC's capacity to support leading players as they promote financial inclusion.  
- E&S: the Project is expected to help UM-ACEP implement an E&S management system and strengthen its capacity to assess E&S-related risks, particularly in the agricultural sector.
